<%cc=@certificate_order.certificate_content%>
<%if @contact.is_a? Contact -%>
Dear <%=[@contact.first_name, @contact.last_name].join(" ")%>,

<%end -%>
Thank you for placing your order. The necessary background checks have been successfully completed and we are pleased to announce that your SSL.com <%=@certificate_order.certificate.description["certificate_type"]%> Certificate for <%=@certificate_order.subject%> has been issued.

We strongly recommend that you follow the installation instructions at <%=Settings.installation_support_pages%> to ensure that your certificate and webserver are correctly configured.

Attached to this email you should find a .zip file containing:

<%if @certificate_order.is_iis?%>
    * Your Certificate (.pb7) - <%=@signed_certificate.friendly_common_name%>.pb7
<%elsif @certificate_order.is_nginx?-%>
    * Your Certificate - <%=@signed_certificate.friendly_common_name%>.chained.crt
<%elsif @certificate_order.is_cpanel? or @certificate_order.is_apache?-%>
    * Your Certificate - <%=@signed_certificate.friendly_common_name%>.crt
    * Your Intermediate Certificates - <%=@signed_certificate.friendly_common_name%>.ca-bundle
<%elsif @certificate_order.is_apache?-%>
    * Your Certificate - <%=@signed_certificate.friendly_common_name%>.crt
    * Your Intermediate Certificates - <%=SignedCertificate::APACHE_BUNDLE%>
<%elsif @certificate_order.is_amazon_balancer?-%>
    * Your Certificate - <%=@signed_certificate.friendly_common_name%>.crt
    * Your Intermediate Certificates - <%=SignedCertificate::AMAZON_BUNDLE%>
<%else-%>
  <%@certificate_order.bundled_cert_names.each do |cc|%>
  <%if @certificate_order.ca == CertificateOrder::CA_CERTIFICATES[:SSLcomSHA2] -%>
    * <%=Certificate::BUNDLES[:comodo][:sha2_sslcom_2014][:labels][cc]%> - <%=cc%>
  <%else-%>
    * <%=Certificate::COMODO_BUNDLES[cc]%> - <%=cc%>
  <%end-%>
  <%end-%>
    * Your Certificate (<%=@signed_certificate.file_type%>) - <%=@signed_certificate.friendly_common_name%><%=@signed_certificate.file_extension%>
<%end-%>

<%if @certificate_order.has_bundle?-%>
Your <%="#{@certificate_order.bundle_name} can be downloaded at: #{server_bundle_csr_signed_certificate_url(cc.csr, cc.csr.signed_certificate)}"%>
<%end-%>

You can also find your <%=@certificate_order.certificate.description["certificate_type"]%> SSL certificate for <%=@certificate_order.subject%> in text format at the bottom of this email.

If you would like your certificate in various other formats or for other server platforms, you can download it from here <%=certificate_order_url(@certificate_order)%>. Please follow the appropriate installation instructions found at <%=SignedCertificate::OTHER_INSTALL_LINK%>.

Other available formats:
<%formats = certificate_formats(@certificate_order)
  formats.each do |k,v|%>
For <%=v[0]%>, please visit <%=v[1]%> (Instructions for <%=v[0]%> can be found here: <%=v[2]%>)

<%end%>
<%if @certificate_order.certificate_duration(:years) > 3-%>

  <%=render(:partial=>"duration_limit")%>
<%end-%>

When you have installed your SSL.com Certificate, be sure to display the secure Smart SeaL. Promoting your secure site is the ideal way to help customers feel safe and confident in using your secure online services and is a proven way to increase conversions.

Get your secure Smart SeaL by visiting the following url - <%=certificate_order_site_seal_url(@certificate_order)%>.

For Smart SeaL installation instructions, please visit https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fwreEDeIf2U

Should you have any questions or issues you would like to discuss, please do not hesitate to contact us.

<%=render(:partial=>"support_contact")%>
<%if @certificate_order.is_iis?%>
<%=@signed_certificate.to_pkcs7%>
<%elsif @certificate_order.is_nginx?-%>
<%=@signed_certificate.to_nginx%>
<%else-%>
<%=@signed_certificate.body%>
<%end-%>